HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 372
BY REPRESENTATIVE WALTERS
VOTERS/VOTING: Creates a subcommittee of the House Committee on House and
Governmental Affairs to study ways to accommodate Louisiana voters with
disabilities
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To create and provide for a subcommittee of the House Committee on House and
3 Governmental Affairs to study ways to accommodate Louisiana voters with
4 disabilities.
5 WHEREAS, voting is a civic duty of paramount importance; and
6 WHEREAS, the right to vote is protected by the Constitution of the United States of
7 America and the Constitution of Louisiana; and
8 WHEREAS, it is important that each Louisiana citizen who is eligible to vote be able
9 to exercise that right; and
10 WHEREAS, the House of the Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana is
11 committed to exploring every possible means that may positively affect the potential for
12 every eligible citizen to participate in the life of their community and state by voting; and
13 WHEREAS, persons with disabilities may face unique hurdles in accessing and
14 executing their ballots and obtaining full assurance that they are counted.
15 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
16 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby create a subcommittee of the House Committee on
17 House and Governmental Affairs to study ways to accommodate Louisiana voters with
18 disabilities, including the procedures available to assist such persons in casting their votes.
